 # Coverage plots for highest-peak chromosome


for(name in names(peak_list)) {
  
  peak <- peak_list[[name]]
  
  # Identify chromosome with the highest peak count
  chr_counts <- table(as.data.frame(peak)[,1])
  chr_counts <- sort(chr_counts, decreasing = TRUE)
  best_chr <- names(chr_counts)[1]
  
  message("Displaying plot for ", name, " on ", best_chr)
  
  # Generate coverage plot and force display in R Markdown
  p <- covplot(peak, chr = best_chr, weightCol = "V5")
  print(p)
}

Since it is difficult to study the difference only via the coverage plots, so we can extract the statistics from the plot:

# Extract coverage statistics for each sample
coverage_stats <- list()

for(name in names(peak_list)) {
  
  peak <- peak_list[[name]]
  
  # Identify chromosome with the highest peak count
  chr_counts <- table(as.data.frame(peak)[,1])
  chr_counts <- sort(chr_counts, decreasing = TRUE)
  best_chr <- names(chr_counts)[1]
  
  # Extract peaks for best chromosome
  peak_df <- as.data.frame(peak)
  chr_peaks <- peak_df[peak_df[,1] == best_chr, ]
  
  # Calculate statistics
  coverage_stats[[name]] <- data.frame(
    Sample = name,
    Chromosome = best_chr,
    Total_Peaks = nrow(chr_peaks),
    Mean_Score = mean(chr_peaks$V5, na.rm = TRUE),
    Median_Score = median(chr_peaks$V5, na.rm = TRUE),
    Max_Score = max(chr_peaks$V5, na.rm = TRUE),
    Min_Score = min(chr_peaks$V5, na.rm = TRUE),
    Mean_Width = mean(chr_peaks$end - chr_peaks$start, na.rm = TRUE),
    Total_Coverage = sum(chr_peaks$end - chr_peaks$start)
  )
}

# Combine into a single data frame
coverage_summary <- do.call(rbind, coverage_stats)
rownames(coverage_summary) <- NULL

print(coverage_summary)

# Function to get unique peaks for KO vs Control
getUniquePeaks <- function(ko_peaks, ctrl_peaks){
  overlaps <- findOverlaps(ko_peaks, ctrl_peaks)
  unique_ko <- ko_peaks[-unique(queryHits(overlaps))]
  unique_ctrl <- ctrl_peaks[-unique(subjectHits(overlaps))]
  list(unique_ko = unique_ko, unique_ctrl = unique_ctrl)
}

# Get unique peaks
foxa1_unique <- getUniquePeaks(peak_GR[["KLF5-KO.FOXA1"]], peak_GR[["Control.FOXA1"]])
elf3_unique  <- getUniquePeaks(peak_GR[["KLF5-KO.ELF3"]], peak_GR[["Control.ELF3"]])

# Annotate unique peaks
annotateUnique <- function(unique_peak){
  annotatePeak(unique_peak, TxDb = txdb, tssRegion=c(-3000,3000), verbose=FALSE)
}

foxa1_KO_anno <- annotateUnique(foxa1_unique$unique_ko)

# Peak files (Using hyphens to match earlier chunks)
peak_files <- list(
  "Control.FOXA1" = "GSM1919987_CFPAC1.wtKLF5_FOXA1_vs_INPUT.CAPAN1_peaks.bed",
  "KLF5-KO.FOXA1" = "GSM1919985_CFPAC1.crKLF5_FOXA1_vs_INPUT.CAPAN1_peaks.bed",
  "Control.ELF3"  = "GSM1919986_CFPAC1.wtKLF5.ELF3_vs_INPUT.CAPAN1_peaks.bed",
  "KLF5-KO.ELF3"  = "GSM1919984_CFPAC1.crKLF5.ELF3_vs_INPUT.CAPAN1_peaks.bed"
)

# Read peaks
peak_GR <- lapply(peak_files, readPeakFile)

# Function to get unique peaks for KO vs Control
# Identifies peaks present in one set but not the other
getUniquePeaks <- function(ko_peaks, ctrl_peaks){
  overlaps <- findOverlaps(ko_peaks, ctrl_peaks)
  unique_ko <- ko_peaks[-unique(queryHits(overlaps))] # Unique to KO
  unique_ctrl <- ctrl_peaks[-unique(subjectHits(overlaps))] # Unique to Control
  list(unique_ko = unique_ko, unique_ctrl = unique_ctrl)
}

# Get unique peaks (Using the hyphen-dot names)
foxa1_unique <- getUniquePeaks(peak_GR[["KLF5-KO.FOXA1"]], peak_GR[["Control.FOXA1"]])
elf3_unique <- getUniquePeaks(peak_GR[["KLF5-KO.ELF3"]], peak_GR[["Control.ELF3"]])

# Annotate unique peaks
annotateUnique <- function(unique_peak){
  # tssRegion=c(-3000,3000) is the standard definition for promoter annotation
  annotatePeak(unique_peak, TxDb = txdb, tssRegion=c(-3000,3000), verbose=FALSE)
}

# Annotate all four unique peak sets
foxa1_KO_anno <- annotateUnique(foxa1_unique$unique_ko)
## >> Using Genome: hg19 ...
